s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:21:"http://ma.tt/?p=41538";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:44:"http://ma.tt/2012/08/state-of-the-word-2012/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1307:"<p>I had an amazing weekend at <a href="http://2012.sf.wordcamp.org/">WordCamp San Francisco</a> hanging out with hundreds of WordPress users from all over the world at the main event and the dev day afterward. Then on Sunday I was humbled to be featured <a href="https://twitter.com/giradesai/status/232314289107660801/photo/1/large">on the cover</a> of my hometown paper the Houston Chronicle <a href="http://www.chron.com/news/houston-texas/article/Houston-born-blog-guru-stays-true-to-his-roots-3763218.php">in an article David Kaplan wrote following the 10-year high school reunion I went to</a> (<a href="http://f.cl.ly/items/1Z2b013T1e380k2P0F1v/2012-07-05-blogging-guru.pdf">PDF</a>).</p>\n<p>If you wanted to catch up on the State of the Word address I gave on Saturday, <a href="http://wordpress.tv/2012/08/06/matt-mullenweg-state-of-the-word-2012/">the video and the slides are now online</a>, or you can watch it embedded below. <a href="http://www.slideshare.net/photomatt/wordpress-state-of-the-word-2012">The slides are on Slideshare</a>.</p>\n<div id="v-M1HXqjrf-1" class="video-player"></div>\n<p>It was a pleasure meeting so many of you, and I hope it&#8217;s not next year before we meet again. Thank you to Michael Pick and Pete Davies for helping me out under tight timelines again.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 07 Aug 2012 03:17:38 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml