(55, 12, '2012-08-17 14:09:02', '2012-08-17 18:09:02', '<strong><span style="font-size: large;">NC&amp;StL General Links</span></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;"><a href="http://groups.yahoo.com/group/ncstl-ps/" target="_blank">The NCSTL-PS Discussion Group</a> - email distribution group related to everything NC&amp;StL (open to the public with registration).</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;"><a href="http://members.fortunecity.com/alanculise/ncstl.html" target="_blank">Photos by H.C. Hill, Sr.</a> - Some of the few surviving photos taken\r\nby Mr. Hill in his capacity of official company photographer for\r\nthe NC from 1915 to 1951. This website is devoted to his memory.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong><span style="font-size: large;">NC&amp;StL Engine 576</span></strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="color: #3366cc; font-size: small;"><a href="http://groups.yahoo.com/group/ncstl576/" target="_blank">The NC&amp;StL 576 Mailing List</a> - <span style="color: #333333;">Discussion group focused on preserving\r\nengine 576</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;"><a href="http://parkengines.railfan.net/TN/" target="_blank">Surviving Steam Photo Archive</a>\r\n- Tennessee</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong><span style="font-size: large;">NC&amp;StL Related Museums</span></strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://cowanrailroadmuseum.org">Cowan Railroad Museum</a></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;"><a href="http://www.jacksonrecandparks.com/leagues/custom_page.cfm?clientid=3046&amp;leagueid=0&amp;pageid=1112" target="_blank">Jackson, Tennesee Depot Museum</a> </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;"><a href="http://www.suncompsvc.com/narm/" target="_blank">Huntsville, Alabama Depot</a> The North Alabama Railroad Museum operates an\r\nAlco S-2 in NC&amp;StL colors.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;"><a href="http://www.tcry.org" target="_blank">Tennessee Central Railroad Museum</a> in Nashville</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;"><a href="http://www.nashvillentrak.org/" target="_blank">Nashville NTrak</a> Modular layouts located at the Tennessee Central\r\nRailroad Museum.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;"><a href="http://www.tvrail.com/">TVRM</a> - Tennessee\r\nValey Railroad Museum, Chattanooga, TN.  NC Deisel #710,\r\nCaboose #41 and more.</span></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.southernmuseum.org"><span style="font-size: small;">Kennesaw GA - Southern Museum of Civil War &amp; Locomotive History</span></a>\r\n- Home of "The General"</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong><span style="font-size: large;">Items of Historical Interest</span></strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://dutchmanscurve.com">Dutchmans Curve</a> - the 1918 wreck - Betsy Thorpe will be releasing her book sometime in 2012.</li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://nashvillenwrr.tripod.com/index.html" target="_blank">Nashville &amp; NW Railroad</a> - a predecessor to the NC&amp;StL</li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;"><a href="http://www.wyndham.com/hotels/BNAUS/main.wnt" target="_blank">Union Station</a>, Nashville Tennessee. Once served by the Flyers, it''s now a hotel.</span></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.andrewsraid.com">The Andrew''s Raid</a>\r\n- Actual facts behind the Great Locomotive Chase involving the\r\nGeneral and the Texas in 1862.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong><span style="font-size: large;">Rail Sites Related to the NC&amp;StL</span></strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.oldncstlrr.8m.com/main.htm"> Abandoned NC&amp;STL Railway: Route between Memphis, Jackson &amp; Bruceton</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.historicsouthpittsburgtn.org/SequatchieValleyRailroad.html" target="_blank">Jasper/Pikeville Branch</a> - Web site of the South Pittsburg Historic Preservation Society.  Information and photos regarding the Sequatchie\r\nValley Railroad leading off the main line at Bridgeport, AL.</li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;"><a href="http://www.trains.com/trn/default.aspx?c=a&amp;id=318" target="_blank">CSX merger family tree</a> on trains.com - Also try a search for NC&amp;StL - will\r\nlist additional articles available.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;"><a href="http://www.srmduluth.org/Features/wanda.htm" target="_blank">SRM Features - Western &amp; Atlantic</a>: "Crookedest Road Under the Sun" - a book\r\nby Col. James G. Bogle, (US Army Retired) that chronicles the\r\nconstruction and operation of the Western &amp; Atlantic Railroad\r\nwhich was later leased to the NC&amp;StL by the State of Georgia.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;">The <a href="http://rayspics.railfan.net/NCSTLSteamers.html" target="_blank">Trains of the South</a> site -- some great photos! </span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;"><a title="Working on the Railroad" href="http://www.pobonline.com/CDA/Archives/5137f0b5ba0f6010VgnVCM100000f932a8c0____" target="_blank">Working on the Railroad</a> - an article written by Bob Baudendistel that\r\nincludes a right of way agreement used by the NC&amp;St.L in 1887.</span></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.math.iastate.edu/jdhsmith/term/slusncsl.htm" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: small;">Dixie Line steam locomotives</span></a><span style="font-size: small;">: a database of\r\nsteam locomotive specifications</span>.</li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;"><a href="http://www.historicmainstreetinn.com/index.htm" target="_blank">Historic Main Street Inn</a> Bed &amp; Breakfast in Wartrace is a railfan\r\nfriendly accomodation.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong><span style="font-size: large;">NC&amp;StL Model Railroading</span></strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;"><a href="mailto:camart62@yahoo.com">Decals</a> for passenger cars, F-3 and F-7 Diesels from Fallen Flags Decals.</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;"><a href="http://www.greatdecals.com/Curt.htm">Decals</a> for NC&amp;StL 2 Bay Hoppers from Curt Fortenberry</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong><span style="font-size: large;">NC&amp;StL Items For Sale</span></strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.crowerrart.com">Watercolors by Frank Crowe</a>\r\n- NC&amp;STL 4-8-2 #558 and NC&amp;STL 4-8-4 #574 rolling a freight\r\ntrain northbound out of Chetoogeta Mtn. tunnel.</li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;"><a href="http://www.rebelrails.com/" target="_blank">Rebel Rails</a> - T-shirts and hats in a wide range of railroads. Check out the NC&amp;StL J-3 hat, mousepads, magnets and more!.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 align="center"><span style="font-size: large;">Submit your favorite NC&amp;StL\r\nlink <a href="mailto:webmaster@ncstl.com?subject=Please%20add%20a%20link%20to%20NCPS%20website">here</a></span></h2>\r\n<p align="center"><span style="color: #000000; font-size: small;">And please add a\r\nlink to NCPS on your website...</span></p>', 'Links of Interest', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'links-of-interest', '', '', '2012-08-17 14:11:06', '2012-08-17 18:11:06', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/ncstl/?page_id=55', 0, 'page', '', 0),
