fault.aspx?c=a&amp;id=318" target="_blank">CSX merger family tree</a> on trains.com - Also try a search for NC&amp;StL - will\nlist additional articles available.</span></li>\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;"><a href="http://www.srmduluth.org/Features/wanda.htm" target="_blank">SRM Features - Western &amp; Atlantic</a>: "Crookedest Road Under the Sun" - a book\nby Col. James G. Bogle, (US Army Retired) that chronicles the\nconstruction and operation of the Western &amp; Atlantic Railroad\nwhich was later leased to the NC&amp;StL by the State of Georgia.</span></li>\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;">The <a href="http://rayspics.railfan.net/NCSTLSteamers.html" target="_blank">Trains of the South</a>\nsite -- some great photos! </span></li>\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;"><a title="Working on the Railroad" href="http://www.pobonline.com/CDA/Archives/5137f0b5ba0f6010VgnVCM100000f932a8c0____" target="_blank">Working\non the Railroad</a> - an article written by Bob Baudendistel that\nincludes a right of way agreement used by the NC&amp;St.L in 1887.</span></li>\n	<li><a href="http://www.math.iastate.edu/jdhsmith/term/slusncsl.htm" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: small;">Dixie\nLine steam locomotives</span></a><span style="font-size: small;">: a database of\nsteam locomotive specifications</span>.</li>\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;"><a href="http://www.historicmainstreetinn.com/index.htm" target="_blank">Historic\nMain Street Inn</a> Bed &amp; Breakfast in Wartrace is a railfan\nfriendly accomodation.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong><span style="font-size: large;">NC&amp;StL Model Railroading</span></strong></h2>\n<ul>\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;"><a href="mailto:camart62@yahoo.com">Decals</a>\nfor passenger cars, F-3 and F-7 Diesels from Fallen Flags Decals.</span></li>\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;"><a href="http://www.greatdecals.com/Curt.htm">Decals</a>\nfor NC&amp;StL 2 Bay Hoppers from Curt Fortenberry</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong><span style="font-size: large;">NC&amp;StL Items For Sale</span></strong></h2>\n<ul>\n	<li><a href="http://www.crowerrart.com">Watercolors by Frank Crowe</a>\n- NC&amp;STL 4-8-2 #558 and NC&amp;STL 4-8-4 #574 rolling a freight\ntrain northbound out of Chetoogeta Mtn. tunnel.</li>\n	<li><span style="font-size: small;"><a href="http://www.rebelrails.com/" target="_blank">Rebel Rails</a> - T-shirts and hats\nin a wide range of railroads. Check out the NC&amp;StL J-3 hat,\nmousepads, magnets and more!.</span><span style="font-size: small;">\n\n</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 align="center"><span style="font-size: large;">Submit your favorite NC&amp;StL\nlink <a href="mailto:webmaster@ncstl.com?subject=Please%20add%20a%20link%20to%20NCPS%20website">here</a></span></h2>\n<p align="center"><span style="color: #000000; font-size: small;">And please add a\nlink to NCPS on your website...</span></p>', 'Links of Interest', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '55-revision', '', '', '2012-08-17 14:08:26', '2012-08-17 18:08:26', '', 55, 'http://localhost:8888/ncstl/55-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
